cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with clustering techniques applied to data represented in a transformed space, which involves learning a representation that is separable into subspaces. This involves techniques from machine learning (transform learning) and subspace clustering. The paper also proposes kernelized extensions to account for non-linearity. Given these aspects, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with text data, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
